e unwilling victims-such as murder, rape, street-level property crime, and white-collar crimelearn to examine several categories of "lifestyle" and "status" deviancedevelop skills for critical analysis of criminal justice and social policiesOverall, students gain an understanding of the sociology of deviance through cross-cultural comparisons, historical overview of deviance in the U.S., and up-close analysis of the lived experience of those who are labeled deviant as well as responses to them in the U.S. today. Instructor Resources are available to easily help with lecture and exam preparation.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 16. Mai 2019) 0aCriminal behavior. 0aDeviant behavior. 0aMental illness. 0aSocial ethics. 0aSocial interaction. 70(DE-601)10458503X0(DE-588)4033178-7aKriminalität2gnd 70(DE-601)1056842870(DE-588)4132883-8aSoziale Norm2gnd 70(DE-601)1061564540(DE-588)4055903-8aSozialverhalten2gnd 70(DE-601)1061938990(DE-588)4047686-8aPsychische Störung2gnd 70(DE-601)1064015560(DE-588)4000320-6aAbweichendes Verhalten2gnd 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2017z978311066755408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018z978311065859040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520965935423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520965935.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018  a978-3-11-065859-0  UCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018  a978-3-11-066755-4  UC Press eBook-Package 2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles